[[!meta date="Sat, 19 Sep 2019 23:00:00 +0000"]]
[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in Tails 3.16"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

[[Tails_4.0|news/version_4.0]] fixes many security issues that affect
Tails 3.16. You should [[upgrade to Tails 4.0|news/version_4.0]] as
soon as possible.

 - Tor Browser: [[!mfsa 2019-33]]
 - Linux: [[!cve CVE-2019-15118]], [[!cve CVE-2019-15117]], [[!cve
   CVE-2019-16714]], [[!cve CVE-2019-14835]], [[!cve CVE-2019-15504]],
   [[!cve CVE-2019-14821]], [[!cve CVE-2019-14814]], [[!cve
   CVE-2019-14815]], [[!cve CVE-2019-14816]], [[!cve CVE-2019-15505]],
   and [[!cve CVE-2019-15538]]
 - CUPS [[!cve CVE-2019-8696]], [[!cve CVE-2019-8675]],
   and more security fixes
 - GnuPG: mitigate the certificates flooding attack
 - e2fsprogs [[!debsa2019 4535]]
 - ghostscript: [[!debsa2019 4518]], [[!debsa2019 4499]]
 - WebKitGTK: [[!debsa2019 4515]]
 - Pango: [[!debsa2019 4496]]
 - ffmpeg: [[!debsa2019 4502]]
 - expat: [[!debsa2019 4530]]
 - GLib: [[!cve CVE-2019-13012]]
 - libmariadb3: numerous vulnerabilities
 - NSS: [[!cve CVE-2019-11719]], [[!cve CVE-2019-11727]],
   [[!cve CVE-2019-11729]]).
 - LibreOffice: [[!debsa2019 4519]], [[!debsa2019 4501]],
   [[!debsa2019 4483]], and [[!cve CVE-2019-9848]]
 - Samba: [[!debsa2019 4513]]
 - OpenSSL: [[!debsa2019 4539]]
 - libxslt: [[!cve CVE-2019-11068]], [[!cve CVE-2019-13117]],
   and [[!cve CVE-2019-13118]]
 - zeromq3: [[!debsa2019 4477]]
 - patch: [[!debsa2019 4489]]
 - Thunderbird: [[!debsa2019 4523]], [[!debsa2019 4482]]
 - wpasupplicant: [[!debsa2019 4538]]
 - IBus: [[!debsa2019 4525]]
 - sudo: [[!debsa2019 4543]]
